SIMPLE: pluralize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pluralize
<hw>Plu"ral*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Pluralized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pluralizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To make plural by using the plural termination; to attribute
plurality to; to express in the plural form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To multiply; to make manifold.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluralize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pluralize
<hw>Plu"ral*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take a
plural; to assume a plural form; <as>as, a noun
<ex>pluralizes</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Earle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>To hold more than one benefice at
the same time.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluralizer</ent>⟦br⟧
